{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":358588,"duration_api_ms":379115,"num_turns":19,"result":"I've identified the root cause of the persistent test failure, but I need your help to apply the fix since both Edit and Bash tools are restricted.\n\n## Root Cause Found\n\nThe `platform-refactor exits 0` test has been failing because of a `set -euo pipefail` interaction in `scripts/sw-hygiene.sh`, in the `scan_platform_refactor()` function (lines 388-392).\n\n**The problem:** Each grep pipeline like:\n```bash\nfallback_count=$(grep -rE \"Fallback:|fallback:\" \"$scripts_dir\" --include=\"*.sh\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\n```\n...exits with code 1 when grep finds **no matches** (which is valid). With `set -o pipefail`, the entire pipeline fails even though `wc -l` + `tr` succeed. `set -e` then kills the script.\n\nThe `info \"Scanning for hardcoded/...\"` message at line 381 runs first (which is why the \"hardcoded\" text check passes), but then the script dies on one of the grep assignments.\n\n**The fix** — add `|| true` to each grep pipeline assignment in `scripts/sw-hygiene.sh` (lines 388-392), and also guard the `find|while|jq` pipeline (line 422):\n\n```bash\n# Lines 388-392 — add || true to each:\nhardcoded_count=$(grep -rE \"hardcoded|Hardcoded|HARDCODED\" \"$scripts_dir\" --include=\"*.sh\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ') || true\nfallback_count=$(grep -rE \"Fallback:|fallback:\" \"$scripts_dir\" --include=\"*.sh\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ') || true\ntodo_count=$(grep -rE \"TODO\" \"$scripts_dir\" --include=\"*.sh\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ') || true\nfixme_count=$(grep -rE \"FIXME\" \"$scripts_dir\" --include=\"*.sh\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ') || true\nhack_count=$(grep -rE \"HACK|KLUDGE\" \"$scripts_dir\" --include=\"*.sh\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ') || true\n\n# Line 422 — add || true:\ndone | jq -s 'sort_by(-.lines) | .[0:15]' 2>/dev/null > \"$sizes_file\" || true\n\n# Line 424 — handle empty sizes_file:\nscript_sizes=$(cat \"$sizes_file\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"[]\")\n[[ -z \"$script_sizes\" ]] && script_sizes=\"[]\"\n```\n\nCould you either:\n1. Enable Edit/Write/Bash permissions so I can apply the fix directly, or\n2. Apply these changes manually to `scripts/sw-hygiene.sh`","stop_reason":null,"session_id":"ef1e1d94-eb09-45d4-b5db-e9e23536bb28","total_cost_usd":1.5590842499999997,"usage":{"input_tokens":21,"cache_creation_input_tokens":61009,"cache_read_input_tokens":1258764,"output_tokens":21535,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":61009,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":21,"outputTokens":21535,"cacheReadInputTokens":1258764,"cacheCreationInputTokens":61009,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.54916825,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":7966,"outputTokens":390,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.009916000000000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Bash","tool_use_id":"toolu_01EzHn143TmM8dji1trTBzEh","tool_input":{"command":"bash scripts/sw-hygiene-test.sh 2>&1 | tail -30","description":"Run hygiene test to see current failure"}},{"tool_name":"Edit","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Bj97KteSju31QnjWcTrZJ8","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/zHardDrive/code/shipwright/scripts/sw-hygiene.sh","old_string":"    local hardcoded_count fallback_count todo_count fixme_count hack_count\n    hardcoded_count=$(grep -rE \"hardcoded|Hardcoded|HARDCODED\" \"$scripts_dir\" --include=\"*.sh\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\n    fallback_count=$(grep -rE \"Fallback:|fallback:\" \"$scripts_dir\" --include=\"*.sh\" 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\n    todo_count=$(grep -rE \"TODO\" \"$scripts_dir\" --include=\"*.sh\" 2>/dev/null |